# Validation Gate (Project Rule)

## Hard constraint

**Do not build new analyzers** until all of the following exist for **5 distinct benchmark channels** (excluding duplicate imports of the same channel):

| Artifact | Path pattern |
| --- | --- |
| `content_dna.md` | `reports/{slug}/content_dna.md` or root `reports/content_dna.md` for reference only |
| `audience_persona.md` | `reports/{slug}/audience_persona.md` |
| `master_emotional_bible.md` | `reports/{slug}/master_emotional_bible.md` |

Count a channel as **complete** only when all three files exist and were produced by running the full pipeline (`main.py` + `bible_synthesizer`) on that channel — not placeholder or copied stubs.

## Allowed work before gate clears

- Bug fixes to existing analyzers and collectors
- **Competitor Acquisition Engine** — discovery, scoring, benchmark YAML updates
- Running existing pipeline on new benchmark channels (`benchmark_program`, `main.py`)
- Report generation and cross-channel synthesis **using existing analyzers**
- Updating `benchmark_channels.yaml` with validated URLs from `reports/channel_candidates.md`

## Forbidden until gate clears

- New analyzer modules (visual v2, motion v2, style evidence engine, knowledge graph, generation)
- New synthesis stages beyond fixing `bible_synthesizer` bugs
- Generation / image / video tooling

## Current priority order

1. Run Competitor Acquisition → `reports/channel_candidates.md`, `TOP_20_BENCHMARK_CHANNELS.md`
2. Full pipeline on top 5 discovered channels
3. Cross-channel synthesis with ≥5 complete channels
4. Only then: Style Evidence Engine or Motion V2

## Reference

WhisprsYT (`whisprs_yt`) counts as **1 of 5** only if per-channel bibles exist under `reports/whisprs_yt/`.
